* Arkness Prime shielded her eyes from the blast with a silver flecked wing, 
but even before it dimmed she stood at the ready. Though Megatron had 
destroyed the cage, he had not terminated the power of the Matrix. And he 
was in for more if he continued to resist.
Her eyes never left Megatron as he landed meters away, though her body 
tensed and fingers gripped the handle of the sword tighter.
Still the Matrix pulsated in her chest, and a shimmer off the sword let 
Megatron know that it was charged with the same deadly energy.
But a slight bit of ammusement simmered deep within at Megatron's 
screeching, though that would not be allowed to destract her.
Arkness Prime took a step towards Megatron, the point of the sword 
extended.*

" I DARE, MEGATRON!"

* Another step taken towards him.*
